{
  "texts": [
    "It substantiates a scientific understanding of the nature of disruptive technological innovation in this context, that can support the development of ethical regulation, guidance, and use cases.",
    "With all this said, using the social system theory, mainly the concept of autopoiesis, we explore how the scientific system, individuals, and technologies like ChatGPT interact and co-evolve (see, for example, Watson and Romic, 2024).",
    "This approach not only broadens the discussion beyond binary choices but also emphasizes the complex interdependencies that characterize the evolution of scientific knowledge and practice in the context of advanced technologies.",
    "By analyzing the debates surrounding generative AI and scientific authorship through the lens of social system theory, we aim to contribute to a better understanding of these technologies' role within the scientific community and society at large.",
    "The conceptualization of a 'system' represents an advance in understanding of the relationship between 'part' and 'whole.'"
  ]
}